id: pm-6pmp
title: "Complete SDK package-author test-assertion surface: service-override + migration helpers"
description: "sdk/testing.ts ships assertRegistered* helpers for 16 of 18 extension register* surfaces. Two remain uncovered: registerService (service overrides, surfaced on ExtensionActivationResult.services) and registerMigration (schema migrations, surfaced on ExtensionActivationResult.registrations.migrations). Package authors testing those registrations must reach into private registry internals, unlike every other registration type. Add assertRegisteredServiceOverride and assertRegisteredMigration to finish the surface."
type: Feature
status: closed
priority: 2
tags[5]: "area:sdk",dx,extensions,living-map,testing
created_at: "2026-06-21T04:21:38.390Z"
updated_at: "2026-06-21T04:59:13.703Z"
author: claude-code-agent
acceptance_criteria: "Add assertRegisteredServiceOverride(services, {service, extensionName?}) and assertRegisteredMigration(registrations, {migration, extensionName?, mandatory?}) to sdk/testing.ts with actionable failure listings matching existing helpers; export both functions + expectation/return types from sdk/index.ts; 100% coverage in sdk-index.spec.ts via real activateExtensionForTest activation + unit branches; document in docs/SDK.md (and fix the stale helper bullet list missing item-field/item-type); pm SDK then covers all extension register* surfaces."
parent: pm-ugqx
resolution: assertRegisteredServiceOverride and assertRegisteredMigration added to sdk/testing.ts and exported from sdk/index.ts; documented in docs/SDK.md; 100% branch coverage. The SDK test-assertion surface is now complete (every extension register* method has a matching assertRegistered* helper).
expected_result: All 18 extension register* surfaces have a first-class SDK assertRegistered* test helper; service overrides and migrations assertable without private registry internals.
actual_result: Delivered both helpers with conventions matching the existing 14 helpers; merged via PR #322; full coverage and all CI gates green.
