notes[2]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-06-21T04:30:41.550Z",claude-code-agent,"Implemented on branch feat/sdk-service-migration-test-helpers. Added two SDK test-assertion helpers to src/sdk/testing.ts: (1) assertRegisteredServiceOverride(services: ExtensionServiceRegistry, {service, extensionName?}) — matches api.registerService overrides surfaced on ExtensionActivationResult.services; case/space-insensitive service-name match; (2) assertRegisteredMigration(registrations: ExtensionRegistrationRegistry, {migration, extensionName?, mandatory?}) — matches api.registerMigration definitions on registrations.migrations by id with optional mandatory-flag assertion (unset flag treated as non-mandatory). Both mirror existing helper conventions (normalize, extension scoping, actionable 'Available ...' failure listings). Exported functions + RegisteredServiceOverrideExpectation/RegisteredMigrationExpectation + return types RegisteredExtensionServiceOverride/RegisteredExtensionSchemaMigrationDefinition from sdk/index.ts. Docs: docs/SDK.md gains both helpers in the bullet list (also added previously-missing assertRegisteredItemField/ItemType) plus worked examples. Tests: tests/unit/sdk/sdk-index.spec.ts +2 activation-path helpers and 4 it() blocks (57 pass), barrel-identity locked. This completes the SDK surface — every extension register* method now has a matching assertRegistered* helper. Manual smoke test from built dist (temp dir, symlinked package) passed: service+migration registered via activateExtensionForTest and both helpers resolved incl. case-insensitive match and actionable failure throw."
  "2026-06-21T04:31:15.619Z",claude-code-agent,"Implemented on branch feat/sdk-service-migration-test-helpers. Added two SDK test-assertion helpers to src/sdk/testing.ts. assertRegisteredServiceOverride(services, expectation) matches api.registerService overrides surfaced on ExtensionActivationResult.services with case/space-insensitive service-name match. assertRegisteredMigration(registrations, expectation) matches api.registerMigration definitions on registrations.migrations by id, with an optional mandatory-flag assertion where an unset flag is treated as non-mandatory. Both mirror existing helper conventions (identifier normalize, optional extensionName scoping, actionable Available... failure listings). Exported both functions plus expectation and return types from sdk/index.ts. Updated docs/SDK.md (helper bullet list now also includes the previously-missing item-field and item-type helpers, plus worked examples). Added activation-path tests in tests/unit/sdk/sdk-index.spec.ts (57 pass) and locked barrel identity. Completes the SDK surface: every extension register-star method now has a matching assertRegistered-star helper. Manual smoke test from built dist in a temp dir with a symlinked package passed."
close_reason: "Shipped in PR #322 (merge 109fafe7). Added assertRegisteredServiceOverride + assertRegisteredMigration to sdk/testing.ts, exported via sdk/index.ts, documented in docs/SDK.md, full branch coverage. Every extension register* method now has a matching assertRegistered* test helper. CodeRabbit-approved (mandatory-flag mismatch message specialized); Sourcery clean; Codex/Gemini not connected."
body: ""
